choices.text:
the rebirth of the Sovereign Mountain Bike Race.

How did this race come about? We were approached by the riders of Team Bianchi, a South African team that races the biggest races across the seas. The team’s aim was to bring together different nations, teams and riders in this race and this was made possible by the support of the Soul Sisters and Serena hotels, who sponsored the event entirely. This being the first year, the team won, however the idea was well received and sport continues to grow and develop.

Likewise, In 2001, Kleansports International, a South African based company that builds and operates mountain bike parks approached the FMD to emulate a championship race from Florencia to Rio de Janeiro in Brazil. A crossbreed of road and technical terrain cycling, Lesotho proved to be a challenge for even the most powerful road riders. With the support of Lesotho’s mountain kingdom, the “Tour of Lesotho” became a reality and is into its fourth year, making it the most prestigious event in the country to date.

With Lesotho still battling with a drought crisis, education is the single thing that Lesotho needs more than ever. Hence its long lasting effect on the country and the long lasting good it does. As in all of these initiatives, it is the women of Lesotho that carry the heaviest burden and it is up to them and us through them that we hope the change will be a lasting one
